Description: Ostracon, large fragment of the shoulder and neck section of a orange-red pottery vessel, interior slightly grooved, exterior covered with a light-brown slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic commodity label.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amarna, el-, House C TA:21-22/603
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393133) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393133)
